        ],
        [
          "A new Brujah to the city, aware of the Promethean Mindset, and wants to demonstrate that it Can work in the modern world, even if one has to apply it more Delicately than they would have in the dark ages.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "For you, life was always about balancing right, wrong, and fun. Your parents were talented performers, so your childhood was interesting and admittedly somewhat unusual. You were always encouraged to follow your passions and pursue what mattered most to you. Even if that wasn't necessarily the way everyone in the crowd was going. Essentially, that if you truly believed that something was right or true, it was only ethical to pursue it to the conclusion, regardless of what popular opinion was. They both did that, and they enjoyed every minute of it, and even though it brought their end, you know they wouldn't have it any other way. From a small child, your own passion was acrobatics, always pushing yourself to the limits of what your body could do and beyond. Finding the limit and surpassing it. Just delighting in the joy of mobility. You're more comfortable in your skin than almost anyone you've ever met, and that didn't change with your death. After all, your parents did die, but that didn't mean you were going to let their death go just like that. It took some time, but you found who and what caused their deaths, and you found a way to bring an end to it. It took allies, teachers, and pushing yourself further than you ever had before. It killed you. Fortunately, one of those allies was a Brujah who thought that the world was better off for having you in it. He brought you over, and taught you all about the history of your new family. All about the glorious ideals of Carthage, and everything since that golden city fell. New powers were yours to test, and new limits as well. Your sire watched over you, keeping you close for a long time, helping you learn to fight, to control your vampiric powers, even to lead a coterie. You clung to the ideals of the Prometheans. A group of Vampires who wanted to bring back the ideals of Golden Carthage. Of Kindred and Kine living together. Helping one another, and living in harmony. It seems only like the right thing to do, given what you are and more importantly, Who. But the Camarilla has never been friendly to Prometheans. In fact in outright executed most of them. But you're patient. You know that it can work. Currently, you can only apply it in small ways. Helping people after the sun goes down. Crushing the odd mugger, trying to keep Vampires from overly abusing humans. But LA is a big city, and there's more than just the Camarilla here. The anarchs have  a more open mind, but they lack unity, and hierarchy. MUCH could be gained if the groups could learn to work together."
        ],
